OL,3,CChildren 'sleeping in baths' because
OL,4,Cparents can't afford beds
OL,6,FA charity which supports families with
OL,7,Fyoung children has said children are
OL,8,Fsleeping in baths because parents
OL,9,Fcan't afford beds.
OL,11,FBaby Basics UK, based in Sheffield,
OL,12,Fsaid it heard regular accounts of
OL,13,Fchildren enduring poor conditions as a
OL,14,Fnew #2.2million scheme was launched to
OL,15,Fprovide beds for all children in under
OL,16,Fthe age of five.
OL,18,FChief executive Cat Ross said: "We are
OL,19,Fhearing horrendous stories of children
OL,20,Fsleeping in baths, on mattresses and
OL,21,Fon sofas."
