OL,3,CChildren 'sleeping in baths' because
OL,4,Cparents can't afford beds
OL,6,FLina is among those who have been
OL,7,Fsupported by the charity after being
OL,8,Freferred by a midwife. She said the
OL,9,Fscheme will make a huge difference.
OL,11,FShe said buying a bed would have meant
OL,12,Fher family "would not have enough
OL,13,Fmoney to buy food and to pay our
OL,14,Fbills".
OL,16,FShe added: "Maybe the electricity will
OL,17,Fcut off or they will cut the water. So
OL,18,Fto us (the initiative) is amazing."
OL,20,FSouth Yorkshire sees some of the
OL,21,Fstarkest health inequalities in the UK.
