OL,3,CChildren 'sleeping in baths' because
OL,4,Cparents can't afford beds
OL,6,FSouth Yorkshire Combined Authority,
OL,7,Fwhich is spearheading the scheme, said
OL,8,Fone in nine newborns in Sheffield
OL,9,Frequired a safe place to sleep last
OL,10,Fyear.
OL,12,FThe programme will apply to families
OL,13,Fwho have been referred by certain
OL,14,Forganisations or agencies.
OL,16,FMayor of South Yorkshire Oliver
OL,17,FCoppard said: "We know that one in
OL,18,Fthree children are in child poverty
OL,19,Facross the country. In South
OL,20,FYorkshire, one in five children are in
OL,21,Fabsolute poverty."
